// Adversarial: Three SpeedBoost effects registered on distinct bump-timing triggers —
// EarlyBumped (0.85x, a slight penalty), PerfectBumped (1.3x), LateBumped (0.9x, mild
// penalty). Dense layout drives frequent bumps to exercise all three timing outcomes.
// Perfect(Random) input randomly assigns bump grades (Early, Perfect, Late) to exercise
// the full timing spectrum including back-to-back mixed timings.
// The adversarial risk: if the trigger bridge incorrectly fires multiple timing variants
// for the same bump event, stacked multipliers compound and blow past BoltMaxSpeed.
// If timing tags are never cleared between bumps, old multipliers accumulate silently.
// BoltSpeedAccurate is the primary detector — it fires the moment bolt speed leaves the
// configured min/max envelope. Godmode breaker ensures infinite play across 5000 frames.
(
    breaker: "godmode",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Perfect(Random),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 6174,
    initial_effects: [
        Stamp(Bolt, Sequence([When(EarlyBumped, Fire(SpeedBoost((multiplier: 0.85)))), When(PerfectBumped, Fire(SpeedBoost((multiplier: 1.3)))), When(LateBumped, Fire(SpeedBoost((multiplier: 0.9))))])),
    ],
)
